    en: "New York General Business Law Article 29-H (Sections 600-603-a) governs the conduct of debt collection agencies and collectors. Combined with 23 NYCRR Part 1 (NY Department of Financial Services debt collection rules, effective 2015), NY imposes disclosure requirements, prohibited practices, and specific consumer protections that exceed the federal Fair Debt Collection Practices Act (15 USC 1692). New York City and Buffalo require debt collection agencies operating in those cities to hold a local license. Statewide, NY does not require general state-level licensing of debt collection agencies, but DFS regulates third-party collector and debt-buyer practices under 23 NYCRR Part 1. Protected consumers can dispute debts, demand validation, and sue for violations. Statute of limitations on most consumer debt is 3 years (CPLR 214-i, changed from 6 years by the 2021 Consumer Credit Fairness Act)."
